Class LimitedFifoObservableList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • javafx.collections.ObservableListBase<E>
          • javafx.collections.ModifiableObservableListBase<T>
            • cern.extjfx.chart.data.LimitedFifoObservableList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of the element kept in the list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, List<T>, Observable, ObservableList<T>

    public class LimitedFifoObservableList<T>
extends ModifiableObservableListBase<T>
    This class provides a limited list with circular behavior. While the list has less elements than the given maximum size, it behaves like a normal observable ArrayList.

    Once the maximum size is reached, adding any new element will also remove the first element, like a FIFO queue would do.

    The list is meant to be used as a container of XYChart.Data when one needs charts presenting live time trends.

    Author:
    Andreas Schaller

      • add

        public boolean add(T element)
        Appends the specified element to the end of this list (optional operation).

        Note, if size() == getMaxSize(), the list won't get longer when adding an element. Instead the first element will be removed.

        Example: 

            list with maxSize = 3 containing [a,b,c]
    list.add(d) will result in [b,c,d]

      • addAll

        public boolean addAll(Collection<? extends T> elements)

        Note, that the given collection will be reduced to the last maxSize elements if needed. If so, the reduced elements will not be added nor removed, so when using a change listener, these elements won't appear in the listeners changes.

        Note, if size() == getMaxSize(), this list won't get longer when adding an element. Instead the first element will be removed.
